Q1. What is an Absolute Number?
     An absolute number means the positive value of any number, we ignore the sign (â€“ or +).
    ðŸ‘‰ Example:
| Number | Absolute value |
| ------ | -------------- |
|  5     | 5              |
| -5     | 5              |
|  0     | 0              |
| -9     | 9              |
or 12 - 18 : -6 but absolute num is 6
   12 - 9  : 3 is also absolute num.


follo up :  write code to find minimum Absolute Number ?
